<section class="page-header">
<div class="container">
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="/blog/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);font-size:0.9rem;text-decoration:none;">← Back to Blog</a></p>
<h1>Closer Than You Think: Car Rental for Tomah, Sparta &amp; Neillsville Drivers</h1>
<p>If you live in Monroe or Clark County and you've been Googling "car rental near me" only to get results in Eau Claire or La Crosse — keep reading.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
<div class="container">
<div style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;">

<p>Here's a small frustration most western Wisconsin drivers know well: you need a rental car, you search online, and the top results route you to the Eau Claire airport (45+ minutes) or La Crosse Regional (also 45+ minutes). The local map is dominated by national chains who price-anchor against airport demand and don't actually have a counter near you.</p>

<p>The closer option is sitting right off Exit 116 on I-94. Riverside Auto Rental has been independently owned and operated in Black River Falls since 1983 — and we're the closest non-chain rental for drivers in Tomah, Sparta, Neillsville, Warrens, Melrose, and most of Monroe and Clark counties.</p>

<h2>The actual drive times (no surprises)</h2>
<div style="background:#f8f9fb;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:32px;">
<ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;">
<li style="padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;"><strong>From Tomah, WI</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-light);">~20 min east on I-94</span></li>
<li style="padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;"><strong>From Sparta, WI</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-light);">~25 min east on I-90/I-94</span></li>
<li style="padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;"><strong>From Warrens, WI</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-light);">~15 min east on I-94</span></li>
<li style="padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;"><strong>From Neillsville, WI</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-light);">~25 min west on WI-54</span></li>
<li style="padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;"><strong>From Melrose, WI</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-light);">~20 min south on WI-54</span></li>
<li style="padding:12px 0;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;"><strong>From Osseo, WI</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-light);">~30 min south on I-94</span></li>
</ul>
</div>
<p>For comparison: from any of those starting points, the Eau Claire airport is 45-70 minutes away. La Crosse Regional is roughly the same. The math favors the local option for almost everyone in this corridor.</p>

<h2>Why this matters more than it sounds</h2>
<p>Renting from an aggregator-routed national chain on a typical "near me" search has three hidden costs:</p>
<p><strong>1. Airport surcharges.</strong> National airport rentals often add facility fees and surcharges on top of the daily rate you see in search results. The local-result number isn't always the number at the counter.</p>
<p><strong>2. Different mileage rules week to week.</strong> Some national chain rate plans bundle limited mileage into the weekly rate, with overage fees beyond a daily cap. Our weekly unlimited rates skip the cap entirely — $450/week for an intermediate car, $750/week for a 15-passenger van. Local-tier weekly rates start lower at $330/week if you're staying within 100 miles per day.</p>
<p><strong>3. Phone trees and call centers.</strong> Try calling an Enterprise or Avis at 4:45 PM with a question about a same-day pickup. Now try calling us at the same time. We answer.</p>

<h2>What's actually in our fleet (and what isn't)</h2>
<p>We don't carry everything. We carry what western Wisconsin actually needs:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:24px;padding-left:20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Intermediate cars</strong> — fuel-efficient, $55/day local (100 mi/day) or $75/day unlimited mileage. Weekly $330 local / $450 unlimited.</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Full-size cars</strong> — more room for road trips and family travel, $65/day local or $85/day unlimited. Weekly $390 local / $510 unlimited.</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>7-passenger minivans</strong> — for families and small groups, $78/day plus $0.10/mile. Weekly $450 (7+ days, unlimited mileage).</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>15-passenger vans</strong> — one of the only providers in western Wisconsin still carrying these, $135/day plus $0.10/mile. Weekly $750 (7+ days, unlimited mileage).</li>
</ul>
<p>What we don't carry: luxury sedans, exotics, or the latest model-year vehicles you'd find at a chain trying to upsell you. Our fleet is reliable, well-maintained, and priced for normal people doing normal things — family reunions, body shop replacements, business trips, sports tournaments, weddings.</p>

<h2>Real renter from the corridor</h2>
<div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:16px;">
<span style="color:#f59e0b;font-size:1.1rem;letter-spacing:1px;" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars">★★★★★</span>
<span style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:600;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">5.0 on Google</span>
</div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-left:4px solid var(--navy);border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
<p style="font-style:italic;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">"My car broke down late at night on my way to a business meeting in Eau Claire. I called Riverside Auto Rental and was able to reach Tas after hours. She immediately arranged a reliable rental for early the next morning so I wouldn't miss my appointment. They truly go above and beyond — saved the day and made a stressful situation stress-free."</p>
<div style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Jim <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">— Eau Claire-bound business traveler</span></div>
</div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-left:4px solid var(--navy);border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
<p style="font-style:italic;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">"I rented a 15-passenger van for a family trip taking my daughters to a volleyball tournament in Kansas City. The entire rental process was completely seamless. Staff is super friendly, quick paperwork, and no hassle at all. The van was a perfect fit for our needs."</p>
<div style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Ben H. <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">— 15-Passenger Van Rental</span></div>
</div>
<p style="margin-bottom:32px;"><a href="https://search.google.com/local/reviews?placeid=ChIJe_gqTAjk_ocRVVpllXYH-zQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:600;">Read all reviews on Google →</a></p>

<h2>What about the body shops?</h2>
<p>Most of the body shops in Tomah, Sparta, and Neillsville already know us. We've worked with adjusters, refinishers, and service writers across western Wisconsin for over four decades. If your shop hasn't worked with us before, ask them to call — most of the time they already have our number.</p>

<h2>The bottom line</h2>
<p>If you live in Monroe or Clark County and you've been driving to Eau Claire or La Crosse for car rentals because that's what showed up on Google Maps, try a phone call to <a href="tel:+17153961466"><strong>715-396-1466</strong></a> instead. We're 20-30 minutes away, the rate at the counter matches what we tell you on the phone, and there's no airport line.</p>

<p>Want details specific to your city? We have dedicated pages for <a href="/locations/tomah.html">Tomah</a>, <a href="/locations/sparta.html">Sparta</a>, <a href="/locations/neillsville.html">Neillsville</a>, <a href="/locations/warrens.html">Warrens</a>, <a href="/locations/melrose.html">Melrose</a>, and <a href="/locations/osseo.html">Osseo</a>.</p>

